Blessing, mother of the deceased 12-year-old student of Chrisland International school, Whitney Adediran, has alleged that the school wants another autopsy done on the remains of her daughter after she has been buried on Thursday. She made this known via her Instagram story on Friday. This comes after Lagos State Government said that the post-mortem report issued by the Lagos State University Teaching Hospital on Wednesday showed that the deceased died from asphyxia and electrocution. Related: Chrisland School: Whitney laid to rest amid tears She wrote, “CHRISLAND!!! Play all your games!!! They just called the police that they want a repeat autopsy. “They want to exhume my daughter’s body for another butchering. These people are a
bunch of jokers!” Whitney died during the school inter-house sports activities at Agege Stadium, Lagos State.